  "title": "WAREHOUSE STOREKEEPER",
  "description": "<p>Key Responsibilities</p>\n<p>1. Warehouse Operations</p>\n<p>•\tReceive, check, and record incoming goods, materials, and equipment.</p>\n<p>•\tProperly store items according to warehouse layout and safety requirements.</p>\n<p>•\tPick, pack, and issue materials based on job orders or delivery requests.</p>\n<p>•\tMaintain cleanliness and organization of the warehouse at all times.</p>\n<p>2. Inventory Control</p>\n<p>•\tConduct regular stock checks and assist in monthly/annual inventory audits.</p>\n<p>•\tEnsure proper labeling, tagging, and tracking of all items.</p>\n<p>•\tUpdate stock records and inventory system accurately and promptly.</p>\n<p>•\tReport any discrepancies or damages to the supervisor.</p>\n<p>3. Forklift Operation</p>\n<p>•\tOperate forklift, pallet jack, and lifting equipment safely and efficiently.</p>\n<p>•\tLoad and unload goods from trucks and containers.</p>\n<p>•\tEnsure proper handling of heavy or bulky materials to prevent damage or injury.</p>\n<p>•\tPerform basic daily checks and report forklift maintenance issues.</p>\n<p>4. Safety &amp; Compliance</p>\n<p>•\tFollow all warehouse safety procedures and company policies.</p>\n<p>•\tEnsure proper use of PPE and maintain a safe working environment.</p>\n<p>•\tAssist in implementing safety improvements and housekeeping initiatives.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>________________________________________</p>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<p>Education &amp; Experience</p>\n<p>•\tMinimum Secondary education or equivalent.</p>\n<p>•\tAt least 1–3 years of warehouse experience preferred.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Licenses &amp; Certifications</p>\n<p>•\tValid Forklift License (WSQ Operate Forklift certification).</p>\n<p>•\tSafety certifications (e.g., OSHA, WSQ) will be an advantage.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Skills</p>\n<p>•\tKnowledge of warehouse operations and inventory systems.</p>\n<p>•\tAble to handle physical work and lift heavy items when required.</p>\n<p>•\tBasic computer skills (inventory entry, simple data updates).</p>\n<p>•\tGood teamwork and communication skills.</p>\n<p>________________________________________</p>\n<p>Additional Information (Optional)</p>\n<p>•\tExperience in construction materials, M&amp;E equipment, or fire protection parts is a plus.</p>\n<p><br></p>",
